we have noted an unhealthy pattern in the fuel_gas  control_valve  servo_current  known as dither karen m dither is a square wave superimposed on the current signal for a control loop the purpose of the dither is to reduce hysteresis of the valve however a high dither setting on control_valve  may contribute to wear on the valve recommendation is to remove the dither settings dither freq= unused ditherampl= refer to til for more information john p the case for not needing the dither can be justified because you can see that even at the different levels of the servo_current  the control is trying to make small adjustments to the position of the valve which means you dont really need the dither signal similar behavior has been seen on kt gt removal of dither settings should also be addressed during next opportunity
